• Total Liabilities: For this balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 5,515,978.61. (No other liabilities are provided.)
• Total Assets: Given as 21,662,106.19.

Step 2: Use the Debt to Asset Ratio formula:
  Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets

Step 3: Calculation:
  Debt to Asset Ratio = 5,515,978.61 / 21,662,106.19 ≈ 0.2546

Step 4: Rounding:
Rounded to two decimal places, the ratio is approximately 0.25.
